title: 34% of the S&P 500's Value Comes From Just 8 Stocks
author: The Motley Fool
description: The S&P 500 index has become highly concentrated, with just 8 stocks making up over 34% of its value. This raises concerns about the market's vulnerability to pullbacks in these 'Fateful Eight' stocks, which have outperformed the broader market. Investors may want to consider equal-weight funds to diversify their exposure.

title: Where Will NuScale Power Stock Be in 10 Years?
author: Leo Sun
description: NuScale Power, a company that develops small modular nuclear reactors (SMRs), has been a divisive stock since its public debut in 2022. While the bulls are excited about its disruptive potential, the bears argue that the stock is overvalued. The company has faced setbacks, including the cancellation of a planned construction project and layoffs. However, the global market for SMRs is expected to grow significantly, and NuScale's first-mover advantage and potential for government funding could drive its future growth.
